Rating: 0
A delicious chili recipe that can be easily adapted to a slow cooker, if desired. I simply sauteed the onion, pepper, garlic, and jalepeno first, then dumped it into a slow cooker w/ the rest of the ingredients and cooked on the low setting for 7 hours. I didn't have zuchinni, so I added an extra can of beans. I correctly guessed that this recipe would not produce enough heat for me, so I used a whole jalepeno and an extra teaspoon or so of chili pepper, and even then it was still what I would consider to be only mildy spicy. Next time I would maybe add a bit of cayenne to the mix. Two other things I would also do differently next time: use unsweetened chocolate instead of semisweet, and drain some of the liquid from the cans of beans before putting them in the mix. The initial results were a little too brothy for me, but this was easily fixed by blending a small portion of the chili in a food processor and then adding it back into the dish.The chili powder & chocolate flavors work really well together in this recipe and produce a rich, dark chili -- especially if you use that extra tablespoon of chili powder. By the second day, the flavors were completely spectacular!

