Not bad. The proportions of the ingredients evidently please a lot of the reviewers who actually followed the recipe. (The only ingredient not found in most other standard recipes is the chocolate, but even that is in some other recipes.) The absence of meat is old-hat for vegetarians. The latter, as well as the thrifty-in-general, would add a significant amount of corn to the mixture or serve the chili with/over brown rice to provide complete protein: the grain (corn or brown rice) provides the amino acids not in the beans, which contain amino acids not in the grain. The beans and the grains together make complete protein. [This information is recalled from Frances Lappe's "Diet for a Small Planet".]

