Rating: 4
I made this chili last year for the super bowl and went looking for it again in my recipe box with the super bowl coming up again. One of our guests is a vegetarian and this is a winner with carnivores and vegetarians alike. I used one zuch and one yellow squash for color. I used the beans as called for, but would easily use whatever beans you favor. Also, not very hot. If you want a hot chili, add more jalapeno, or habanero or whatever you think you need. Finally, regardless of the chili recipe, at the end I always add in a little bit of a cornstarch and water slurry. In addition to thickinening the chili, it adds a silky, lustruous look to the chili that just makes it look like more than chili. Got the tip from Cook's Illustrated and will never pass it up. Looking forward to this chili again for the Super Bowl and the leftovers. That's all for now.

